@notice Emitted when a relay server registers or updates its details.
 Looking up these events allows a client to discover registered Relay Servers.
@return The block number in which the contract has been deployed.
@return The maximum age the relay is considered registered by default by this `RelayRegistrar`, in seconds.
@notice Change the maximum relay registration age.

@notice Emitted when a relay server registers or updates its details.
 Looking up these events allows a client to discover registered Relay Servers.
@return The block number in which the contract has been deployed.
@return The maximum age the relay is considered registered by default by this `RelayRegistrar`, in seconds.
@notice Change the maximum relay registration age.

returns._0: The block number in which the contract has been deployed.

params.relayHub: The address of the `RelayHub` contract for which this action is performed.
params.relayManager: An address of a Relay Manager.

returns.info: All the details of the given Relay Manager's registration. Throws if relay not found for `RelayHub`.

returns._0: The maximum age the relay is considered registered by default by this `RelayRegistrar`, in seconds.

params.relayHub: The address of the `RelayHub` contract for which this action is performed.

returns.info: The list of `RelayInfo`s of registered Relay Servers

params.maxCount: The maximum amount of relays to be returned by this function.
params.oldestBlockNumber: The latest block number in which a Relay Server may be registered.
params.oldestBlockTimestamp: The latest block timestamp in which a Relay Server may be registered.
params.relayHub: The address of the `RelayHub` contract for which this action is performed.

returns.info: The list of `RelayInfo`s of registered Relay Servers

params.relayHub: The address of the `RelayHub` contract for which this action is performed.
params.url: The URL of the Relay Server that is listening to the clients' requests.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

RelayServerRegistered(address,address,by.notice: Emitted when a relay server registers or updates its details. Looking up these events allows a client to discover registered Relay Servers.

readRelayInfos(address).notice: Read relay info of registered Relay Server from an on-chain storage.

readRelayInfosInRange(address,uint256,ui.notice: Read relay info of registered Relay Server from an on-chain storage.

registerRelayServer(address,bytes32[3]).notice: This function is called by Relay Servers in order to register or to update their registration.

setRelayRegistrationMaxAge(uint256).notice: Change the maximum relay registration age.

userdoc.notice: The on-chain registrar for all registered Relay Managers.The client can use an implementation of a `RelayRegistrar` to find relay registration info.
